utterances.sentences: I hate those guys.

utterances.sentences: -- he's trying to do his job. I just think that for reporters it never works out if you become the story. Do you remember a few years ago when John McCormack got pushed in a scuffle?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: And he got pushed down and he didn't want to be part of the story and everyone tried to make it into this whole thing how he was pushed by the Democratic candidates' guy. So, I wouldn't have done the whole thing at CNN. Like ignore it. Let -- he's going to have to go back to the Capitol every single day and do his job. So why blow it up into a big thing and say it's disgusting and demand apologies? That I didn't think was right. Now, however, I think the United States senators who are paid by the taxpayers who are answerable to their constituents and through the press, I don't think -- it didn't seem like her to me. Now she's -- maybe she's had it. And I get it. She's a fighter pilot but she's also in a very tough race in Arizona. And she got a lot of Atta girls from people from the right and I think that's one of the things that she was thinking.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: Jesse?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Well, you know, Juan, I don't engage in name-calling. I don't like to bash the media.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: OK.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: I think they do a great job. So, I'm not going to -- no. I think you're right. I think all of these senators talk trash about reporters. They just don't do it to their face. She did it to his face and all hell broke loose. And then I thought to myself, how many times have senators and congressmen on the left said nasty stuff about us at Fox News? They have called us lunatics, hacks, conspiracy theorists. Things a lot worse.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: And there's there --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Like a lot of people did.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: And then there's the inaccurate stuff.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: You know, we don't go around and cry and put out press releases.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: And go on Hannity shows.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: No.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: We would never act like the victim. When you're called names like that. But listen, he's not a hack but he's a liberal. He goes around and asks questions from a liberal perspective. He doesn't ask Chuck Schumer where is Hunter. He asks McSally, do you think we should call witnesses? That's fine. That's his job.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: But everybody is being asked, they are going to have to answer on Tuesday.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Yes, but they're answering questions from the Democratic perspective.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.sentences: Maybe -- maybe they have beef. Maybe they have an issue. Maybe he tweeted something about her or said something and she just continued to carry it. But he knows and every reporter who works in that gaggle knows that you have to have an explosive bite in order to get on. Because they do that all day long. They chase people around and every single interaction is not going to get on. But something like that is. And it's lonely and it's tough especially when other people gang up on you. It's a win-win for everyone.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Do you think this is good for Manu?

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.sentences: I think -- I think it's good for him because all of his friends at CNN get to cry and they're like, how dare they. And they act so offended. And then people in Arizona are like I didn't know she had it in her. Good for her.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: Hey, Greg.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.sentences: Because they probably have the same level of frustration. And you know, I've seen Joe Biden be so disrespectful to Peter Doocy. I think sometimes Peter Doocy asks some questions and he knows that the vice president is going to get very upset with him.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Yes. If sleepy Joe puts one finger on one hair of Peter Doocy's beautiful head, he's going to have to answer to me.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: Really?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: What about his father? His dad -- OK. But let's look at Laura Ingraham asks Senator McSally the same question.

utterances.speaker: INGRAHAM
utterances.sentences: What about Manu Raju's questions? Do you want witnesses?

utterances.speaker: MCSALLY
utterances.sentences: Well, I want a fair trial. Do it again in the House.

utterances.speaker: INGRAHAM
utterances.sentences: OK. You're not going to play the game --

utterances.speaker: MCSALLY
utterances.sentences: No, no, no.

utterances.speaker: INGRAHAM
utterances.sentences: You can call me a conservative hack. But do you want witnesses, yes or no? Why aren't you telling us?

utterances.speaker: MCSALLY
utterances.sentences: Because we're going to vote on Tuesday to start the trial and let them present --

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: Wow. So, Laura Ingraham says, I guess she is a conservative hack if Manu is a liberal hack.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: No because we -- let's avoiding the obvious here. The beef is about the network. This is a network that has pushed a three-year hoax. OK?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Right.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: So, everybody on the other side is like I'm tired of this crap. They also push the most anti-law enforcement narrative I've ever seen on TV before Trump was in office. So, there's an inherent bias about dividing America. I do hope that Manu gets the medical help that he needs for this grievous, grievous injury. Do they have a therapy llama in your bio or a therapy fairy that can keep him company? I just hope he's all right. I think that the word hack is not a good word. I think it's a lazy word. I don't think he's a hack. I think there are better words to come up with. But I think it's incredibly healthy for people in this world to view the press the same way that they look at pyramid schemes. That the only way the press can maintain power is to get you to believe in their story. And the sooner you realize that, the healthier you are. So the more antagonism towards the media there is, the better I feel. And I'm saying that as somebody who is in the media, but I loathe the media.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: Yes, I noticed.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Self-loathing.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: All right, there's another media controversy brewing. It's over this New York Times op-ed headline, Megan McCain has a problem -- The View has a problem with Megan McCain. The piece goes on to say, "for some viewers, Miss McCain is the privilege product of conservative nepotism, capitalism, and the American military-industrial complex." Miss McCain responding on Twitter, "If the New York Times wants to understand the country, maybe they should try having one woman in the room who doesn't accept their groupthink on guns, abortion, and religion. Apparently, that's too much for them." Ladies?

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.sentences: Megan --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Are you referring to me?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: You know I wouldn't do that.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.sentences: Megan works really hard. And she's worked hard for a long time. She's worked in media for a long time. And she's definitely put her time in. And the reason people talk about her is because she researches her topics and challenges people that otherwise conservative journalists wouldn't have access to. And, you know, I think there are disloyal people who work at her show, who have personal agendas, and they're servicing their own careers and the media by planting these stories. And I think it's a bad look, not only for The View but for ABC, and they need to clean up their culture.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: But has any show ever had this sustained amount of disarray and disgruntlement for years way before even Megan McCain got this?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: What about this show?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Well, we don't get in it -- but I think it's different because we laugh about it.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: We love each other. We laugh and we love. Look, you know what kills me about this story is that they published this article. It was like a crank letter. You know when somebody writes to Fox? Those girls on T.V. at THE FIVE, their skirts are too short, and Greg Gutfeld uses bad language. I heard him use "damn" the other day. I'm turning off the set unless Juan apologizes. It's a crank letter. The New York Times published a crank letter because friends in high places, right? There's somebody at ABC who's friends with somebody at the Times, because there's no way that would have been published if it wasn't --

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: But also, how many of these people -- like I'm surprised at how many reporters watch The View and then write about it every day.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Well, because they're home then.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Yes, I guess.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: They're home. What?

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.sentences: They're also being -- they're also being (INAUDIBLE) that stuff. And again, like lock it up, you guys. Have some loyalty for where you work, the organization, and the show.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: I wrote a big piece on Jessie anonymously and that's coming out next week.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: Jesse, give me your take. Because some people are Abby Huntsman, all the things that have been checked. Is that conservative versus conservative?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: I think she does a good job on that show. She's outnumbered. She's like the Juan Williams of The View. She gets paid very well to be the lone voice and she gets paid well to take a beating. And yes, you know, her name is McCain so that opens doors. Just like Hunter Biden's name opens doors in Ukraine. One person is very talented without the last name an one's not. And one gets everything, Hunter, because of who he is. She can stand on her own.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: You think you got a thing going for Hunter today?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Where is he, Juan?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: All right, all right, here we go. Stay right there folks, the "FASTEST SEVEN," a whole lot of Friday fun coming up for you next on THE FIVE.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.sentences: Bet you. We just betted. All right, welcome back. It's time for the "FASTEST SEVEN." First up the LSU Tigers were at the White House today, but it's what happened right after at the big football game that's getting all the attention. There is an arrest warrant out for NFL star OBJ Odell Beckham Jr. after he did this in the locker room. He spanked his bottom. The cop apparently wanted to punch back him in the face, but kept his cool then saw the video and later press charges. Jesse, what do you make of this?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: He shouldn't have been slapping the cop around like that. But the cop doesn't need to be in the locker room trying to crack down on champions smoking cigars. Why are they in the locker room? They're trying to celebrate? Get the cops out of there. Let them celebrate.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: He what's -- he wasn't a cop. That was actually a stripper. They hired a stripper.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: You know, that should be Odell's defense.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Yes. I thought he was -- I thought he was --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: I thought he was taking his clothes off.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Don't strippers dress up as cops.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: It happens to me every time.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.sentences: We did that once to one of our executives at the MTV Beach House because the cops kept showing up with noise complaints. And so one showed up and she started crying because she thought the cops are there to arrest her. And then he's like -- but you know, can't you celebrate. You win the national championship. And then another police officer came in, it's like, smoke your cigars, boys.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Yes. So there's plenty of other things that are happening in New Orleans where you would need officers' attention, smoking cigars, although I can't really imagine how much smoke was in there. I probably would have had to leave myself.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: Yes, that's my feeling. I think a lot of things going on locker rooms, a lot of ass smacking, a lot of --

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.sentences: What? That's right, Juan.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: -- profanity, and lot of crazy.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: He's taking us back to the 80s.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: But I must say, I must say, if you are in a locker room in this era, you should be aware of cameras, you should be aware of cell phones. And I guess you have to be aware, Jesse, of police, because I've never been in a locker room where they've been police but I don't think this is working. So he smacks the guy. He didn't smack him in the face. He touched -- in the locker room, how many guys are whipping towels.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Yes, he was saying good game.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: That should be his defense.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Right.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.sentences: Up next, we've seen standing desks and treadmill desks, Bret Baier has one, and those weird ball chairs that people still sit on, but could this be the next big office trend. Behold, the lie-down desk. It lets you work while flat on your back. You just lie down. Not cheap. It costs over $7,000. Do you already have one, Greg?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Working horizontally? Isn't that what the Mustang Ranch is for? You kids don't understand. I am sick and tired of people making light of just normal sitting. We are made to sit OK. I'm tired -- I don't -- when I walk by my coworkers that are standing, I kick their legs out. I kick their legs out. They fall down and they ride in pain. And I say, get a damn chair because you're hurting the chair business. They're putting big chair out of business.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: You have a lot of money tied up in big chairs?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: I got all my stocks. My 401(k) is all big chair. High chair as they call it.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.sentences: So Dana, is it -- is it a placebo effect because some of the reviews online like I'm so creative and productive now that I'm lying down.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: It's like the -- it's like the weighted blanket craze and everyone thought they needed a weighted blanket so they could go to sleep. Like you don't really need one. You don't need it. I got a balance board to be standing on at my standing desk.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Balance board?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Oh my god.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.sentences: My 10-year-old has a hoverboard. And she just hovers around the apartment with her laptop open.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: I sit in a bath of hot oil.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.sentences: That might explain your mood.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: You said -- you said Bret Baier has what?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Treadmill desk.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: So he runs while he --

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.sentences: No, he walks. He said he can -- he can clock like six miles a day on that thing. It's very impressive.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Really.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: I tell you what's impressive, the cost of this thing. So in other words --

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: This is like you could get a peloton. I think some people here have done it for -- I think you goodbye like almost three pelotons for this thing. So what is this about? This is like an indulgence?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: It's not about --

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.sentences: Do you -- do you remember the movie Wally where people are so fat in the future, they just like, glide around in these chairs because they can't stand up and they eat out of cups. That's it. We're turning into Wally like we're so stupidly lazy that we can't even be bothered to sit up and work. I Must recline.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: But it might help your back a little bit, or your front.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.sentences: Finally, have you been sick with the flu this season? It turns out our booming economy may be to blame -- seriously. Researchers say job growth is bringing more people into the workplace, and that could increase the spread of the virus. Greg, you've always said you like to be the infected monkey.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.sentences: You like to be the person --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: You know, it's kind of -- I have the same philosophy about zombies. It's like, why are you scared of zombies? Just become one and then people are scared of you, right? This study is wrong. It's because of the holidays. The holidays cause the flu because people are on planes. And with a good economy, they're flying more, so everybody spread it. Like my wife and I, we got the flu coming back from your damn wedding. I was in bed for six days because of you, Jesse.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.sentences: Yes, but you lost weight. You look great.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Thank you.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: You were late to the wedding, Greg.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Well, yes.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: And I still haven't gotten a gift, by the way. Was my gift your presence at the wedding?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Yes, that was the present.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: You know, I think the bigger problem is people don't get the flu shot. The vaccine thing.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: That is true.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: This is like, all right, people going to get the flu, but why we have the sense in America -- and I run to so many people, oh, I don't get the flu shot. I think I get sick if I get the flu shot. Get the flu shot, will you?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: It's true though. Like the economy is good so people -- the planes are packed, people are traveling either for business but -- or for fun, and that's -- it does spread so you have to just be careful. You know, take care of yourself.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Dana, they're blaming Trump for the flu. That's what this is.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: No, actually -- no, no, no.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: The economy is so good --

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Turn it around, Jesse. Turn it around and say it is a great sign that there's the flu because President Trump has given us the greatest economy so now we can have more flu. It's fabulous.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: That's right?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: That's how you turn it around.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.sentences: Don't go anywhere. "FAN MAIL FRIDAY" is up next.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: I love sticks. All right, it's "FAN MAIL FRIDAY," answering your questions. First question from Kristine S. If you film your own commercial for the Super Bowl, what item would it be for, Jesse?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Probably that lay down chair.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: I'd probably have a sponsorship with the laydown chair. And you can just fake like you're sleeping when you're supposed to be working. That's what that's about.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: OK.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: First of all, price tag of $7,000.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Dana?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Healthy dog food.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Oh, interesting.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Then you have -- like I could have Jasper in the commercial.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Of course.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: And I could get some promote -- some like free dog food.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Oh, there you go. Always working the angle. That's what they say, the Dana angle, working the Dana angle, Juan.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: That's what they said?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: That's what they say.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: Wait a second. So I got -- I can think of three categories. So beer.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: Beer has got to be big, right?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: Then snack food. Snack foods is got to be big, and cars.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: So I think I would pick snack food.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: OK.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: I like the toes as my kids call the Doritos, Fritos.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: And human toes.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: They're not bad, either.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: I have a whole jar of them in the basement.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Grose.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: What was that era when I used to pick up drifters? Kennedy.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.sentences: I think I would like -- I would like to sell hot freedom.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Hot freedom.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.sentences: I'm not sure what it is, but I think it's a full-body rub.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.sentences: You just rub it all over your body and all of a sudden, you love the Constitution in these United States of America.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: I would sell a combination, my pillow, Tommy John underwear. It's underwear that you can use as a pillow or a pillow that you can wear as underwear.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.sentences: That's brilliant.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: And make it gold.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: And make gold, exactly.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: No, no, no, silver.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Silver.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Sorry, silver.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: And you can keep -- and you can keep it in your safe. All right, what's in your safe? All right, what is the one thing you are embarrassingly bad at, Dana?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: I don't know.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Oh, good, pretend like you can't think of something. Come on, Dana.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: No, I mean, I'm bad at all sorts of things. I don't know. I probably have to say a sport, probably.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: OK, sports.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Jesse.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: I'm a really bad singer.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: I'm a terrible singer.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: You can't have mine. Like in church, like I'm so meek and church. The minute I say one thing, people start looking around. That's why I don't go to church.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: That's true. I did stop going to church because I don't like the singing part.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: I'm just bad singer. I don't like to sing.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: I also -- I also don't like the handshaking thing.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Yes?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Because I don't want -- I don't want --

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: But the economy is great so you could get the flu.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Kennedy?

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.sentences: I'm bad at acting.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Oh, yes.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.sentences: Really, really bad. And so the creator of CSI New York was like I wrote a part for you and it is yours. All you have to do is come read it. And they're like, oh, you're really bad at acting. I'm sorry, we can't go with you.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Juan?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: You know, when I go to the beach, all the guys go out in the ocean. We try to do handstands and I will try and try and flip and flop and the wave comes and knocks me down and try again. I'm just -- I'm --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: You flipflop all the time.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.sentences: That's it.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Is you family trying to kill you?

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.sentences: I'm bad at saying no.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: I think James -- the Dems hate him more than Trump.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Well, I'm just so --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: So, the guy has got bad instincts. And every time you call him out on it, he puts out on this boy scout routine.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: OK. All right. So, he's not --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: He's a dirty cop.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: I don't know about a dirty cop.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: He's not a cop.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: That's wrong.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: That's -- OK. But that's actually law enforcement officers do not like James Comey because he doesn't understand their culture or the world. They come from it. It is always all about him. It's never about the people in the FBI.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: It is always about him. You're right.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: And unfortunately, under him, federal law enforcement has really suffered.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: And their reputation has suffered. And he allowed that and Andrew McCabe allowed that. And the fact that he was, you know, like a dirty lawyer nefariously leaking stuff to the New York Times and the Washington Post through an intermediary, that he admitted. He said that was the impetus for the Mueller investigation for launching that. He knew that would happen --

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: But that's not what this is about.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: -- upon his firing.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: This is a witch hunt. You both of you just --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Witch hunt.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: OK. But --

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: You don't like James Comey.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: I know --

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: I may not like James Comey.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Juan said with hunt.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Why are you going back in time to go after this guy?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: He --

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: Because those are the facts that happen to bolster the case --

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: That what?

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: -- that he had a screw loose and he's a bad person.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Fine?

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: He's a bad person with so much power, he could use the entire apparatus at his disposal to spy on a political campaign.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: And the FBI they are trying to rehabilitate their reputation of the FBI. And a state bureau chief -- a state level bureau chief would have been fired for the same thing.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I'd like to go back and use a little of history to help everybody out here. Remember back in the 90s there was a TV show called "Friends." A very popular show. Remember how disappointed you were when you sit down to watch "Friends" and the episode would be about Phoebe?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes. And you're like I don't really care about Phoebe.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Well Comey is the Phoebe of American politics. I mean, he's always there in the background but I really don't want to hear about him anymore.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: You want to hear about Ross.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I think I want to hear about Ross or Joey.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: And Rachel.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: They were funny people. But it's like I feel like when he comes on, I feel like I'm watching episode two of series three. I've already gone through it. We know they all die at the end of "Friends," by the way.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Very sad.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: That's in the last season. They all die.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: I didn't know that.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: yes. Yes. But Comey, Comey got famous and he enjoyed being famous. He should be a spokesman for a product, I was thinking something like depends. And you know, when you really need to stop a leak and he could just be sitting there and he's like very comfortable. Anyway.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: The Flex Seal that would be a good one.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: That Flex Seal that's a great one.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Why not?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Why not?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I would like to do Lactaid or Sequel.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Or the other one we're talking about in the commercial break.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes. We're not going to talk about that.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: The other one. The other one.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: I think Trump could do those new light bulbs for the --

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: All right. Coming up, CNN furious with Republican Senator Martha McSally over what she said to a reporter. We're going to show you next.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: It's a media uproar over this exchange between a CNN reporter and Republican Senator Martha McSally.

utterances.speaker: MANU RAJU, SENIOR CONGRESSIONAL CORRESPONDENT, CNN
utterances.utterance: Senator McSally, should the Senate consider new evidence as part of the impeachment trial?

utterances.speaker: SEN. MARTHA MCSALLY (R-AZ)
utterances.utterance: Manu, you're a liberal hack. I'm not talking to you.

utterances.speaker: RAJU
utterances.utterance: You're not going to comment, Senator?

utterances.speaker: MCSALLY
utterances.utterance: You're a liberal hack.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Wow. After McSally said that, CNN hosts raced to defend their colleague. Look at this.

utterances.speaker: WOLF BLITZER, HOST, CNN
utterances.utterance: It was disgusting, it was awful. She should know better. She or her staff no one has reached out to apologize to you, have they?

utterances.speaker: RAJU
utterances.utterance: I have not heard from them at all, Wolf.

utterances.speaker: CHRIS CUMO, HOST, CNN
utterances.utterance: This question was obvious. So was her dodge, so was the disrespect. It's all textbook Trump. She really acted like a punk.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Whoa! And here's Senator McSally responding.

utterances.speaker: MCSALLY
utterances.utterance: I'm a fighter pilot. You know? I called it like it is. And that's what we see out of the mainstream media and especially CNN every single day. So obviously I'm going to -- I'm going to tell the truth. The Democrat senators walk by and they say hi, how are you today and then they chase after the Republicans.

utterances.speaker: LAURA INGLE, FOX NEWS CORRESPONDENT
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: MCSALLY
utterances.utterance: I mean, it's honestly ridiculous.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: All right. She can have a problem with CNN but I don't think that reporter's opinion -- that's not Joe Scarborough. So, I just thought it was over the top. But they certainly responded. You have to have thick skin if you're a reporter, powerful people are not going to like you if you're reporting the news. Dana, you have a lot of experience with news and being on either side of that fence. Do did you find that?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: You should have seen what I used to call reporters behind their backs.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: I'm kidding. I'm kidding. I'm kidding. So, OK. A couple of things. Manu Raju I think is actually a very good reporter.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: I agree.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: And you see him he works -- you see him he's always there along with our Chad Pergram, our Mike Emanuel walking the halls. He's working --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I hate those guys.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: -- he's trying to do his job. I just think that for reporters it never works out if you become the story. Do you remember a few years ago when John McCormack got pushed in a scuffle?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: And he got pushed down and he didn't want to be part of the story and everyone tried to make it into this whole thing how he was pushed by the Democratic candidates' guy. So, I wouldn't have done the whole thing at CNN. Like ignore it. Let -- he's going to have to go back to the Capitol every single day and do his job. So why blow it up into a big thing and say it's disgusting and demand apologies? That I didn't think was right. Now, however, I think the United States senators who are paid by the taxpayers who are answerable to their constituents and through the press, I don't think -- it didn't seem like her to me. Now she's -- maybe she's had it. And I get it. She's a fighter pilot but she's also in a very tough race in Arizona. And she got a lot of Atta girls from people from the right and I think that's one of the things that she was thinking.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Jesse?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Well, you know, Juan, I don't engage in name-calling. I don't like to bash the media.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: OK.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: I think they do a great job. So, I'm not going to -- no. I think you're right. I think all of these senators talk trash about reporters. They just don't do it to their face. She did it to his face and all hell broke loose. And then I thought to myself, how many times have senators and congressmen on the left said nasty stuff about us at Fox News? They have called us lunatics, hacks, conspiracy theorists. Things a lot worse.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: And there's there --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Like a lot of people did.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: And then there's the inaccurate stuff.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: You know, we don't go around and cry and put out press releases.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: And go on Hannity shows.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: No.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: We would never act like the victim. When you're called names like that. But listen, he's not a hack but he's a liberal. He goes around and asks questions from a liberal perspective. He doesn't ask Chuck Schumer where is Hunter. He asks McSally, do you think we should call witnesses? That's fine. That's his job.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: But everybody is being asked, they are going to have to answer on Tuesday.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Yes, but they're answering questions from the Democratic perspective.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: Maybe -- maybe they have beef. Maybe they have an issue. Maybe he tweeted something about her or said something and she just continued to carry it. But he knows and every reporter who works in that gaggle knows that you have to have an explosive bite in order to get on. Because they do that all day long. They chase people around and every single interaction is not going to get on. But something like that is. And it's lonely and it's tough especially when other people gang up on you. It's a win-win for everyone.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Do you think this is good for Manu?

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: I think -- I think it's good for him because all of his friends at CNN get to cry and they're like, how dare they. And they act so offended. And then people in Arizona are like I didn't know she had it in her. Good for her.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Hey, Greg.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: Because they probably have the same level of frustration. And you know, I've seen Joe Biden be so disrespectful to Peter Doocy. I think sometimes Peter Doocy asks some questions and he knows that the vice president is going to get very upset with him.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Yes. If sleepy Joe puts one finger on one hair of Peter Doocy's beautiful head, he's going to have to answer to me.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Really?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: What about his father? His dad -- OK. But let's look at Laura Ingraham asks Senator McSally the same question.

utterances.speaker: INGRAHAM
utterances.utterance: What about Manu Raju's questions? Do you want witnesses?

utterances.speaker: MCSALLY
utterances.utterance: Well, I want a fair trial. Do it again in the House.

utterances.speaker: INGRAHAM
utterances.utterance: OK. You're not going to play the game --

utterances.speaker: MCSALLY
utterances.utterance: No, no, no.

utterances.speaker: INGRAHAM
utterances.utterance: You can call me a conservative hack. But do you want witnesses, yes or no? Why aren't you telling us?

utterances.speaker: MCSALLY
utterances.utterance: Because we're going to vote on Tuesday to start the trial and let them present --

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Wow. So, Laura Ingraham says, I guess she is a conservative hack if Manu is a liberal hack.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: No because we -- let's avoiding the obvious here. The beef is about the network. This is a network that has pushed a three-year hoax. OK?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Right.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: So, everybody on the other side is like I'm tired of this crap. They also push the most anti-law enforcement narrative I've ever seen on TV before Trump was in office. So, there's an inherent bias about dividing America. I do hope that Manu gets the medical help that he needs for this grievous, grievous injury. Do they have a therapy llama in your bio or a therapy fairy that can keep him company? I just hope he's all right. I think that the word hack is not a good word. I think it's a lazy word. I don't think he's a hack. I think there are better words to come up with. But I think it's incredibly healthy for people in this world to view the press the same way that they look at pyramid schemes. That the only way the press can maintain power is to get you to believe in their story. And the sooner you realize that, the healthier you are. So the more antagonism towards the media there is, the better I feel. And I'm saying that as somebody who is in the media, but I loathe the media.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Yes, I noticed.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Self-loathing.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: All right, there's another media controversy brewing. It's over this New York Times op-ed headline, Megan McCain has a problem -- The View has a problem with Megan McCain. The piece goes on to say, "for some viewers, Miss McCain is the privilege product of conservative nepotism, capitalism, and the American military-industrial complex." Miss McCain responding on Twitter, "If the New York Times wants to understand the country, maybe they should try having one woman in the room who doesn't accept their groupthink on guns, abortion, and religion. Apparently, that's too much for them." Ladies?

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: Megan --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Are you referring to me?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: You know I wouldn't do that.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: Megan works really hard. And she's worked hard for a long time. She's worked in media for a long time. And she's definitely put her time in. And the reason people talk about her is because she researches her topics and challenges people that otherwise conservative journalists wouldn't have access to. And, you know, I think there are disloyal people who work at her show, who have personal agendas, and they're servicing their own careers and the media by planting these stories. And I think it's a bad look, not only for The View but for ABC, and they need to clean up their culture.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: But has any show ever had this sustained amount of disarray and disgruntlement for years way before even Megan McCain got this?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: What about this show?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Well, we don't get in it -- but I think it's different because we laugh about it.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: We love each other. We laugh and we love. Look, you know what kills me about this story is that they published this article. It was like a crank letter. You know when somebody writes to Fox? Those girls on T.V. at THE FIVE, their skirts are too short, and Greg Gutfeld uses bad language. I heard him use "damn" the other day. I'm turning off the set unless Juan apologizes. It's a crank letter. The New York Times published a crank letter because friends in high places, right? There's somebody at ABC who's friends with somebody at the Times, because there's no way that would have been published if it wasn't --

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: But also, how many of these people -- like I'm surprised at how many reporters watch The View and then write about it every day.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Well, because they're home then.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Yes, I guess.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: They're home. What?

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: They're also being -- they're also being (INAUDIBLE) that stuff. And again, like lock it up, you guys. Have some loyalty for where you work, the organization, and the show.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I wrote a big piece on Jessie anonymously and that's coming out next week.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Jesse, give me your take. Because some people are Abby Huntsman, all the things that have been checked. Is that conservative versus conservative?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: I think she does a good job on that show. She's outnumbered. She's like the Juan Williams of The View. She gets paid very well to be the lone voice and she gets paid well to take a beating. And yes, you know, her name is McCain so that opens doors. Just like Hunter Biden's name opens doors in Ukraine. One person is very talented without the last name an one's not. And one gets everything, Hunter, because of who he is. She can stand on her own.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: You think you got a thing going for Hunter today?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Where is he, Juan?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: All right, all right, here we go. Stay right there folks, the "FASTEST SEVEN," a whole lot of Friday fun coming up for you next on THE FIVE.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: Bet you. We just betted. All right, welcome back. It's time for the "FASTEST SEVEN." First up the LSU Tigers were at the White House today, but it's what happened right after at the big football game that's getting all the attention. There is an arrest warrant out for NFL star OBJ Odell Beckham Jr. after he did this in the locker room. He spanked his bottom. The cop apparently wanted to punch back him in the face, but kept his cool then saw the video and later press charges. Jesse, what do you make of this?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: He shouldn't have been slapping the cop around like that. But the cop doesn't need to be in the locker room trying to crack down on champions smoking cigars. Why are they in the locker room? They're trying to celebrate? Get the cops out of there. Let them celebrate.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: He what's -- he wasn't a cop. That was actually a stripper. They hired a stripper.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: You know, that should be Odell's defense.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes. I thought he was -- I thought he was --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: I thought he was taking his clothes off.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Don't strippers dress up as cops.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: It happens to me every time.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: We did that once to one of our executives at the MTV Beach House because the cops kept showing up with noise complaints. And so one showed up and she started crying because she thought the cops are there to arrest her. And then he's like -- but you know, can't you celebrate. You win the national championship. And then another police officer came in, it's like, smoke your cigars, boys.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Yes. So there's plenty of other things that are happening in New Orleans where you would need officers' attention, smoking cigars, although I can't really imagine how much smoke was in there. I probably would have had to leave myself.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Yes, that's my feeling. I think a lot of things going on locker rooms, a lot of ass smacking, a lot of --

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: What? That's right, Juan.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: -- profanity, and lot of crazy.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: He's taking us back to the 80s.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: But I must say, I must say, if you are in a locker room in this era, you should be aware of cameras, you should be aware of cell phones. And I guess you have to be aware, Jesse, of police, because I've never been in a locker room where they've been police but I don't think this is working. So he smacks the guy. He didn't smack him in the face. He touched -- in the locker room, how many guys are whipping towels.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Yes, he was saying good game.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: That should be his defense.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Right.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: Up next, we've seen standing desks and treadmill desks, Bret Baier has one, and those weird ball chairs that people still sit on, but could this be the next big office trend. Behold, the lie-down desk. It lets you work while flat on your back. You just lie down. Not cheap. It costs over $7,000. Do you already have one, Greg?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Working horizontally? Isn't that what the Mustang Ranch is for? You kids don't understand. I am sick and tired of people making light of just normal sitting. We are made to sit OK. I'm tired -- I don't -- when I walk by my coworkers that are standing, I kick their legs out. I kick their legs out. They fall down and they ride in pain. And I say, get a damn chair because you're hurting the chair business. They're putting big chair out of business.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: You have a lot of money tied up in big chairs?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I got all my stocks. My 401(k) is all big chair. High chair as they call it.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: So Dana, is it -- is it a placebo effect because some of the reviews online like I'm so creative and productive now that I'm lying down.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: It's like the -- it's like the weighted blanket craze and everyone thought they needed a weighted blanket so they could go to sleep. Like you don't really need one. You don't need it. I got a balance board to be standing on at my standing desk.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Balance board?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Oh my god.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: My 10-year-old has a hoverboard. And she just hovers around the apartment with her laptop open.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I sit in a bath of hot oil.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: That might explain your mood.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: You said -- you said Bret Baier has what?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Treadmill desk.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: So he runs while he --

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: No, he walks. He said he can -- he can clock like six miles a day on that thing. It's very impressive.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Really.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: I tell you what's impressive, the cost of this thing. So in other words --

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: This is like you could get a peloton. I think some people here have done it for -- I think you goodbye like almost three pelotons for this thing. So what is this about? This is like an indulgence?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: It's not about --

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: Do you -- do you remember the movie Wally where people are so fat in the future, they just like, glide around in these chairs because they can't stand up and they eat out of cups. That's it. We're turning into Wally like we're so stupidly lazy that we can't even be bothered to sit up and work. I Must recline.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: But it might help your back a little bit, or your front.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: Finally, have you been sick with the flu this season? It turns out our booming economy may be to blame -- seriously. Researchers say job growth is bringing more people into the workplace, and that could increase the spread of the virus. Greg, you've always said you like to be the infected monkey.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: You like to be the person --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: You know, it's kind of -- I have the same philosophy about zombies. It's like, why are you scared of zombies? Just become one and then people are scared of you, right? This study is wrong. It's because of the holidays. The holidays cause the flu because people are on planes. And with a good economy, they're flying more, so everybody spread it.
